{
  "doc_id": "15802",
  "text": "One of the suggested mechanisms for a positive effect of selenium on child cognition is protection against oxidative stress through the antioxidative properties of selenoproteins. Selenium plays an important role in the protection of neurons to a large extent through selenoprotein P, which is a major contributor to selenium content in the brain [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In addition, antioxidative glutathione peroxidases have been shown to be highly active in glial cells [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , and thioredoxin reductases appear important for cerebellar function [CITATION_5] . In addition, selenium is essential for thyroid function [CITATION_6] , which is important for child development.",
